This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new algorithm for online learning using kernel approximation. It may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves adapting the model on-the-fly. Additionally, the use of feature maps suggests that it could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the use of gradient descent suggests that it could be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
